  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Flood Response in Muqur district, Badghis province</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To respond to the flash floods in Muqur district, Badghis Province. Overall target is 710 HH or 4,970 persons. Type of response Response: 1. Provide 325 HHs (2,275 families) with a one-time unconditional cash assistance 2. Provision of conditional cash assistance 385 HHs (2685 families) to undertake rehabilitation of irrigation canals and water catchments. 3. Distribution of water treatment packets and hygiene kits through WVs complimentary sources. 4. Establish community based flood preparedness and readiness structures and train them on early warning messaging</narrative>
  </description>
